<item>
            <title>[FLINK-27222] Execution history limit can lead to eviction of critical local-recovery information</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-27222</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Local recovery relies on knowing the allocation id of the last deployment. To that end we iterate over all previous execution attempts and use the last &lt;tt&gt;assignedAllocationID&lt;/tt&gt;, if any.&lt;br/&gt;
However, since the execution history is bounded (to, by default, 16 entries) this can lead this information being evicted.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In other words, with the default configuration (history limit = 16, restart delay = 1s) local recovery can only kick if the TM is restarted within 16 seconds.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should decouple this information from the execution (history).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
